reviews.name: Chelsea P.
reviews.review: Literally the worst people ever. I had a cargo van with me to unload a bed and bed frame. Keep in mind I LIVE at THE PARAMOUNT. My rent is paying for their salary. I was parked for no more than 10 minutes bringing things up to my apartment and coming down. The man demands my keys and told me he will go park if it it disturbs anyone. I said I will be leaving once I finish bringing the bed upstairs and he said okay but to still give him the keys. I come back down no more than 4 minutes later and the van has been moved and they were demanding me to pay for an hour of parking. Telling me I cant just leave the van parked there. Like are you guys fucking idiots? Did you clearly not see me running up and down to move things in? I wasn't just leaving the van there for fun and games. The stupid dude NEVER TOLD ME IF I STAYED THERE, THEY WILL CHARGE ME. HE JUST ASKED FOR THE KEYS AND GAVE ME SOME BULLSHIT EXCUSE. I argued my way out of it and was able to leave without paying. Literally the worst people. I literally fucking live there.

Also, their elevator was broken the entire time I parked there.

reviews.name: Steve W.
reviews.review: This was my first experience using this garage and it was very nice. It was clean, staff were friendly and helpful, and everything went smoothly. I was there for a work related event and drove a Camry. I was able to find a spot alongside a wall and had to wiggle my way in backwards, but, I had no problems finding a spot and being able to pay ahead via the web was beneficial.

reviews.name: Cindy O.
reviews.review: My experience with this garage was FANTASTIC. Very easy to prepay, hands down, a great place to park. The attendant was very nice and even pointed to the best exit in order to get to AT&T. I felt extremely comfortable leaving my car there, I am for sure going to keep using this service!

reviews.name: Sylvia M.
reviews.review: I have parked here several times and it was,always a great place however this this time I can not say that. Being a weekday there was only valet parking and we barely walked 25 feet from my car and I heard my car turn on and watched as the attendent burned rubber both backing up and after moving my car from one place to another then deny he did it even though my sons and I watched him do it. Turns out he was the manager Alex who was rude and had zero people skills. I finally got him to agree to just let me park my own car since I had prepaid parking however I can't believesomething like this is allowed. Do not plan on returning unless I am allowed to park my own car, the valet service is horrible. I do not drive my car that way and expect valet to respect others property as well. Very upsetting experience!

reviews.name: Rajath
reviews.review:
It was wonderful and hassle free, even the reservation through parkme.com
portal was simple & user friendly. Even I have tried first time to use

Thanks and I'm sure with good customer service any business would flourish
and all the best for you guys !

reviews.name: Bruce C.
reviews.review: The website was super easy and fast. Parking garage was excellent. Have already used the service again.

reviews.name: Wmark S.
reviews.review:
I use this lot all of the time for going to Giants games. First time I used ParkMe was for  game 5 of NLCS. There were spots available when we arrived, so I'm not sure how well the reservations part works when the lot is full, but it did save us $3 off the fee we would have paid if we just paid when we left. You just need to make sure you are out by 11 if you are using ParkMe.

BTW, every time I have parked here, the attendants are very helpful/friendly.
